The Northern Governors Forum has felicitated with former President Olusegun Obasanjo on his 85th Birthday. Chairman of the Forum and Plateau Governor Simon Bako Lalong, in a statement, described Obasanjo as a nationalist and passionate leader whose patriotism is paramount in all his engagements. Lalong said at 85, Obasanjo continues to offer his wise counsel to leaders at various levels as well as participate in national dialogue aimed at tackling insecurity, poverty, disease and intolerance.   FG to stem quackery in MDAs with digital stamps     I stopped 50 consultants from collecting revenue in Niger…     Nigeria can end Boko Haram insurgency, terrorism using…   He said the former President has never hidden his belief in the unity, oneness and indivisibility of Nigeria and continued to encourage the younger generation to be positive and shun all actions that will erode national unity, peace and development. Lalong said the Northern Governors Forum appreciates his fatherly counsel and personal interventions towards finding lasting solutions to insecurity in Nigeria, particularly in the Northern Region. Lalong, in a statement by his spokesman, Dr. Makut Simon Macham, wished him many more years of good health and God’s protection, urging him never to relent in lending his voice towards a greater Nigeria.